sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: the origin sequence of this part comes from BioBrick BBa_E1010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: this part is a intermediate part, to see the detail design consideration please go to BBa_K371021

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K371024
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part is not long, so it can be easily get by direct annealing two oligonucleotides.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a short amino sequence used to link or fuse two protein domain together to make a large chimera protein.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: different codons of Gly and Ser was choosed in order to ignore the mismatch between forward sequence and reverse sequence when they are annealing.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang Zhang

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K371037
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This parts is a fusion protein between pduA protein and RFP protein(BBa_E1010). At each end is special DNA sequence that make this parts compatible to BBF RFC 53. The MPF and MSF is the abbreviation of meta-prefix and meta-suffix seperately. Because pduA is said to be the shell protein of pdu BMC, this part can be used to direct pduA-RFP chimera into BMC lumun.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yang Zhang
